The line was long and slow. There was one lady running the register, answering the phone and getting orders together. She was rude and short with the patrons. The floor was so sticky and dirty it pulled the shoe off my foot. The tables were sticky and nasty and there was a large pile of boxes and other trash by the door that impeded the line to order. The service was extremely slow and no one acted like they wanted to be at work. The menu boards were gone and there was a minimal selection of items to chose from. When I inquired about the normal menu I was told, “what do you want?” I ordered two slices of extreme meats and 5 lemon and pepper wings. I was not provided a receipt either. She also did not have enough change in the register to provide me with the exact change. It was only .06 but it’s the point. I was shocked by the service and appearance of the store. I’ve dined there many times before and the atmosphere was always good, service okay, and food delicious. I am not sure what happened today. I will never return and eat there again. When I received my food the wings were placed on top of the pizza and a receipt was placed on top of the wings. When I went to speak with the manager I was bluntly told with no apologize or anything, “what do you want? You want a refund or pizza?” I asked for a refund and she asked for a receipt. I explained that I was not given one. She then asked me what I ordered and I told her my order. She provided me a refund that was LESS than what I originally paid. So, I left hungry and with less cash than I walked in the door with. Fuel you charge too much money for what I experienced today. Please step your game up to match your prices!
